# ticket-to-tests skill routing

## When to invoke the skill

Apply the `/ticket-to-tests` skill automatically when the user:

- Asks to write, review, extend, or refactor automated tests for any service or feature
- Mentions a Jira ticket key alongside test writing, test design, or evaluation
- Asks to sync tests with Zephyr Scale or evaluate test quality
- Asks to run `evaluate_test_quality.py` or check API coverage

Do not start writing test code until all phases of the skill workflow have been applied
(or the user explicitly skips specific phases). Named phases: 1, 2, 3, 3b, 4, 5, 5b, 5c, 6, 7, 7b.

## Phase routing rules

| Trigger | Required phase |
|---|---|
| User provides a Jira ticket URL or key | Phase 2 via `mcp-atlassian` first — do not skip |
| Feature modifies an existing endpoint | Phase 3b (feature impact analysis) — after Phase 3, before Phase 5 |
| User asks to push/export to Zephyr | Always dry-run first; never live-create without explicit confirmation |
| User asks to evaluate test quality | Run `~/.agents/skills/ticket-to-tests/tools/evaluate_test_quality.py` |
| User asks to check API coverage | Run `~/.agents/skills/ticket-to-tests/tools/update_api_coverage.py` |
| User has not specified a target environment | Prompt for `TARGET_ENV` before Phase 3 |
| Tests run and failures found during Phase 5c | Apply §3j triage; confirm before each Jira bug; annotate SKIP_XFAIL |

